Say hello to <b>Roshaan</b>, our featured Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Roshaan has been chilling out at her <a href="http://millsberry.com/home/?user=rose_roshaan">Metro Park pad at <a href='/home/?user=rose_roshaan'>39008-D Triumph Boulevard</a></a>, since moving to town on June 18th, 2007. As you might have guessed, she's also been loving life in Millsberry and taking advantage of all it has to offer.  <br><br>Roshaan describes herself as very charming and friendly. So if you meet her, watch out! You may be best buds in no time. <br><br>Roshaan also thinks of herself as creative. It's no wonder that one of her interests happens to be painting! And, if you're hanging out with Roshaan, be on the lookout for karate chops! She's way into martial arts, too. <br><br>Another one of Roshaan's interests is basketball. No wonder she's got a trophy for Sink Three! Not that she's a stranger to gold. Roshaan's racked up a total of 15 trophies&mdash;though she's also stayed active in the community, participating in Millsberry Match Wanted, the Peabody Park Cleanup, and Walk for Malawi. <br><br>When she's not helping out around town, Roshaan's likely to be hanging out at one of her favorite spots: her best friend's house, the tree house, or school. Roshaan loves to learn, but she can also teach you a thing or two about your dance steps. Some of her favorite music is salsa.<br><br>The next time you see Roshaan, be sure to congratulate her and thank her for being such an outstanding citizen!</div>
